'''D'Anthony Smith''' (born June 9, 1988) is an [[American football]] [[defensive tackle]] for the [[Louisiana Tech Bulldogs football|Louisiana Tech Bulldogs]]. He is currently a senior at the school. He played high school football at [[Pickering High School]].

==Early years==
Smith was born in [[Berlin]], [[Germany]], but eventually immigrated to [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]]. At Pickering High School, Smith played three sports, [[American football|football]], [[basketball]] and [[shot put]]. He started all four years at the school, and every year but one, he received an award for his play on the defensive line. As a senior at the school he had 80 tackles and three sacks.<ref name="Tech">{{cite web|url=http://www.latechsports.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/smith_danthony00.html|title=#5 D'Anthony Smith|work=[[Louisiana Tech University]]|accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref>

==College career==
In his collegiate debut as a true freshman in 2006, Smith [[Interception (American football)|intercepted]] a pass that was deflected by another player against [[Nebraska Cornhuskers football|Nebraska]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncf/recap?gameId=262450158|title=No. 20 Nebraska amasses 584 yards of offense in rout|date=September 2, 2006|work=[[Associated Press]]|accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref> Smith overall, started eight games and came off the bench in five for the Bulldogs and had 38 tackles. His career high in tackles came against [[North Texas Mean Green football|North Texas]] when he had seven, he also had five against [[Fresno State Bulldogs football|Fresno State]].<ref name="Tech" />

Against Fresno State as a sophomore in 2007, Smith equaled his total from the season before with five tackles, but also added a [[Quarterback sack|sack]] on their [[quarterback]] [[Tom Brandstater]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://espnradio.espn.go.com/ncf/playbyplay?gameId=272720278&period=0|title=Louisiana Tech 6, Fresno State 17|date=September 29, 2007|work=ESPN.com|accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref> For the season, he started 11 games and missed one due to injury and had 42 tackles and three sacks. Smith tied his career high in tackles with seven against [[Central Arkansas Bears|Central Arkansas]].<ref name="Tech" />

Against [[San Jose State Spartans football|San Jose State]] in 2008, Smith had seven tackles and one sack.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://fresnostate.scout.com/a.z?s=164&p=2&c=810156|title=Big Win on the Road  |last=Jones|first=Jason|date=November 10, 2008|work=[[Scout.com]]|accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref> Heading into the [[2008 Independence Bowl|Independence Bowl]] against [[Northern Illinois Huskies football|Northern Illinois]], he lead the team five sacks and was third with 65 tackles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.seattlepi.com/scorecard/cfootballnews.asp?articleID=247932|title=Bulldogs and Huskies square off in Independence Bowl|date=December 28, 2008|work=[[Seattle Post-Intelligencer]]|accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref> He was named as a member of the First-team All-[[Western Athletic Conference|WAC]] following the regular season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tri-cityherald.com/1412/story/396897.html|title=These WAC players are award-winning performers|last=Cripe|first=Chadd|date=November 25, 2008|work=[[Tri-City Herald]]|accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref> For the season, he had nine tackles on two occasions and was named All-Louisiana. He started every one of the Bulldogs's 13 games.<ref name="Tech" />

